"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166618","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-10-31","<p>​The British Government is aware of unconfirmed reports of human rights violations during recent protests in Eswatini. We continue to call for respect of the freedoms of expression, peaceful assembly and association enshrined in Eswatini’s constitution. The appointment of a resident High Commissioner to Eswatini in July 2019 has given us the opportunity to deepen our engagement with the Eswatini government. Our High Commissioner has raised the need for proportionate response to protest with senior officials in the Eswatini Government. On 24 October he also raised with the Ministry of Foreign Affairs the need for any allegations of human rights violations to be investigated.</p>","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson",,"2019-10-31T16:12:28.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166618/answer","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166618/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166618/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-10-28","Eswatini: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the human rights situation in Swaziland.","false","Biography information for Conor McGinn","St Helens North","Conor McGinn","6438"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166619","Cabinet Office","false","2019-10-31","<p>The Register to Vote website has undertaken two essential maintenance windows so far in October 2019. The service was offline from 8:30am to 10:30am on Friday 4th October and Friday 25th October. This maintenance is essential to ensure the service remains secure and fit for purpose.</p><p>We are always looking for improvements to the service including reducing the downtime required for maintenance work.</p><p> </p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2019-10-31T17:36:43.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166619/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166619/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166619/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-10-28","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster and Minister for the Cabinet Office, on what dates the online register to vote service has been offline as a result of scheduled maintenance; and for how many hours it was offline on each of those days in October 2019.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","6343"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166620","Cabinet Office","false","2019-10-31","<p>The Register to Vote website has had no downtime so far in October 2019 as a result of non-scheduled maintenance or non-maintenance issues.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2019-10-31T15:39:35.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166620/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166620/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166620/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-10-28","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster and Minister for the Cabinet Office, on what dates the online register to vote service has been offline as a result of (a) non-scheduled maintenance and (b) non-maintenance issues; and for how many hours it was offline on each of those days in October 2019.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","6344"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166621","Department for Transport","false","2019-10-31","<p>To date, drivers in the St Helens metropolitan borough have benefitted from grant funding for the installation of 125 domestic chargepoints, under the electric vehicle home charge scheme, and for the installation of 11 sockets, under the workplace charging scheme. Both of these schemes remain open for motorists of St Helens choosing zero emission vehicles.</p><p> </p><p>St Helens metropolitan borough are also able to claim a grant towards the installation of chargepoints under the On-street Residential Charging Scheme; however as at this point in time, they have not yet made an application.</p><p> </p><p>St Helens has also benefitted from the £4,701,629 awarded to Arriva and Merseytravel for 72 Biomethane, Electric and Hybrid buses, and £280,720 for accompanying charging infrastructure.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2019-10-31T13:25:39.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166621/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166621/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166621/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-10-28","Electric Vehicles: St Helens","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 21 October 2019 to Question 1062 on Electric Vehicles: Charging Points, what grant funding his Department has allocated to St Helens Borough Council to increase the number of electric car charging points in that Borough.","false","Biography information for Conor McGinn","St Helens North","Conor McGinn","6439"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166622","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-11-05","<p>Public Health England (PHE) has run a number of Be Clear on Cancer (BCOC) campaigns to help improve early detection of cancer, including bowel cancer.</p><p>In 2017, PHE ran a pilot campaign in the East and West Midlands which focussed on a range of abdominal symptoms, such as diarrhoea, bloating and discomfort that can be indicative of several cancers, including bowel cancer.</p><p>In January 2017, PHE and Cancer Research UK ran a regional BCOC campaign across the North West of England, aimed at increasing participation of 60 – 74-year olds in the English National Health Service Bowel Cancer Screening Programme.</p><p>Decisions on which cancers Be Clear on Cancer campaigns should focus on are informed by a steering group. This decision is under constant review, informed by the available data and medical information resources.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bury St Edmunds","Jo Churchill",,"2019-11-05T11:59:53.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166622/answer","Biography information for Jo Churchill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166622/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166622/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-10-28","Bowel Cancer: Health Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what recent steps he has taken to increase public awareness of the symptoms of bowel cancer.","false","Biography information for Ben Bradley","Mansfield","Ben Bradley","6506"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166623","Cabinet Office","false","2019-10-31","<p>The cost of the public information campaign will be published monthly on a rolling basis, as part of routine government transparency arrangements.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith","6461","2019-10-31T17:56:03.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166623/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166623/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166623/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-10-28","Brexit: Publicity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster and Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much has been spent from the public purse by each supplier on the Get Ready for Brexit campaign as of 28 October 2019.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","6206"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166624","Cabinet Office","false","2019-10-31","<p>“Get Ready for Brexit” is a public information campaign that provides the facts citizens and businesses need to know about the preparations they need to take to be ready for when the UK leaves the EU.</p><p>The campaign aims to reach as many UK citizens and businesses as possible and to ensure key messages are delivered to groups most likely to need to take action before the UK leaves the EU.</p><p> </p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2019-10-31T15:37:21.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166624/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166624/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166624/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-10-28","Brexit: Publicity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster and Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of the number of members of the public his Department plans to inform through the Get Ready for Brexit campaign.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","6207"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166625","Cabinet Office","false","2019-10-31","<p>The ‘Get Ready for Brexit’ campaign is being paused and reviewed following the EU’s agreement to a Brexit extension until 31 January.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2019-10-31T15:36:58.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166625/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166625/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166625/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-10-28","Brexit: Publicity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster and Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether the Get Ready for Brexit campaign remains operational.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","6208"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166626","Cabinet Office","false","2019-10-31","<p>There are no plans to publish the business case for the ‘Get Ready for Brexit’ campaign; as has been the usual practice of successive administrations regarding officials’ advice to Ministers.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2019-10-31T15:43:05.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166626/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166626/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166626/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-10-28","Brexit: Publicity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster and Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will publish the business case for the Get Ready for Brexit campaign.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","6209"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166627","Cabinet Office","false","2019-10-31","<p>The “Get Ready for Brexit” campaign has not received any official notification of complaints from the Advertising Standards Agency in relation to its advertising.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2019-10-31T15:46:13.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166627/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166627/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166627/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-10-28","Brexit: Publicity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster and Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many complaints have been made to the Advertising Standards Agency about the Get Ready for Brexit campaign.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","6210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166628","Cabinet Office","false","2019-10-31","<p>“Get Ready for Brexit” is a public information campaign that provides the facts citizens and businesses need to know about the steps they need to take to be ready for when the UK leaves the EU.</p><p>The campaign has used a broad range of advertising platforms across print (including national and regional newspapers), broadcast (including national and regional radio and TV stations) and digital media (including multiple social media platforms and news websites), in both the UK and other EU27 countries.</p><p>The campaign aims to reach as many UK citizens and businesses as possible and to ensure key messages are delivered to groups most likely to need to take action before the UK leaves the EU.</p><p> </p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2019-10-31T15:38:00.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166628/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166628/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166628/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-10-28","Brexit: Publicity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster and Minister for the Cabinet Office, in which (a) print, (b) broadcast and (c) digital media outlets advertising space has been purchased for the Get Ready for Brexit campaign.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","6211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166629","Cabinet Office","false","2019-10-31","<p>50 FTE in GDS act as central support and coordination for developing the Digital, Data and Technology profession across government. However, each department has their own DDaT professionals who also support the delivery of the digital transformation agenda.</p>","Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire","Simon Hart",,"2019-10-31T15:47:24.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166629/answer","Biography information for Simon Hart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166629/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166629/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-10-28","Government Departments: Digital Technology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster and Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 22 October 2019 to Question 1565, how many civil servants co-ordinate the work of the approximately 17,000 Digital, Data and Technology professionals employed across government and directly supporting delivery of the Digital Transformation Strategy.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","6212"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166630","Cabinet Office","false","2019-10-31","<p>Of the 15,508 DDaT professionals we have validated, so far, as part of the recent DDaT workforce commission (July 2019), there are approximately 9,955 civil servants, 3,469 contingent workers and 2,084 professionals with an unreported resource type.</p><p> </p>","Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire","Simon Hart",,"2019-10-31T15:42:42.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166630/answer","Biography information for Simon Hart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166630/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166630/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-10-28","Government Departments: Digital Technology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster and Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 22 October 2019 to Question 1565, how many of those 17,000 Digital, Data and Technology professionals are (a) directly employed civil servants and (b) contingent workers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","6213"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166631","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-10-31","<p>Statistics on the Work Programme, including information on starts, referrals and job outcomes is published and available here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/work-programme-statistics--2" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/work-programme-statistics--2</a></p><p> </p><p>Statistics on the Work Choice programme, including information on starts, referrals and job outcomes is published and available here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/work-choice-statistics-number-of-starts-and-referrals--2" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/work-choice-statistics-number-of-starts-and-referrals--2</a></p>","Eastleigh","Mims Davies",,"2019-10-31T17:46:47.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166631/answer","Biography information for Mims Davies","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166631/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166631/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-10-28","Employment Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people are participating in (a) the Work Programme and (b) Work Choice; and on what date the final participants will complete those programmes.","false","Biography information for Margaret Greenwood","Wirral West","Margaret Greenwood","6405"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166632","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-10-31","<p>My right hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Defence has spoken to NATO counterparts on various occasions about a range of topics, most recently at the NATO Defence Ministerial meeting on 24-25 October. The UK has repeatedly raised concerns at Ministerial and official level about the Turkish purchase of S-400 missiles.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2019-10-31T15:00:47.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166632/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166632/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166632/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-10-28","Turkey: Guided Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent discussions he has had with his NATO counterparts on the potential effect of Turkish missile systems on UK air operations against Daesh.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","6177"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166633","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-11-04","<p>The property in question was temporarily used by troops from the Royal Electrical and Mechanical Engineers as part of Exercise Iron Viper 2019 which ran from 23 September to 3 October. The exercise was a routine test of the Army's logistical and technical support capabilities which also involved units from the Royal Engineers, Royal Corps of Signals, Royal Logistic Corps and Royal Army Medical Corps. To achieve realism, the exercise utilised both the Defence estate and private land, including a number of sites in urban areas.</p>","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Anne-Marie Trevelyan",,"2019-11-04T14:34:46.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166633/answer","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166633/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166633/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-10-28","Royal Electrical and Mechanical Engineers: Swindon","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reason the Royal Electrical and Mechanical Engineers Corps have moved to the former Clares factory in Swindon.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","6214"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166634","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-10-31","<p>My right hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Defence has raised our concern about Turkey's acquisition of the Russian S-400 missile system with both our Turkish and wider NATO counterparts. Turkey is a valued NATO Ally, on the front line of some of the UK and the Alliance's most difficult security challenges. Defence equipment procurement decisions are for individual nations, but all NATO allies have committed to reducing their dependence on Russian-sourced military equipment.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2019-10-31T15:05:15.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166634/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166634/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166634/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-10-28","Turkey: Guided Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent discussions he has had with his (a) Turkish counterpart and (b) NATO counterparts on Turkey's acquisition of Russian anti-air missile systems.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","6178"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166635","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-10-31","<p>Defence has developed a prudent standby package of Defence personnel to support the civil authorities on a range of tasks if required. There are no plans to utilise military personnel for public order following Brexit and the Armed Forces have not undertaken urban training exercises in preparation for the UK leaving the EU without a deal. Defence routinely conducts training and exercising in a range of environments, including urban environments as part of its preparedness for overseas operations.</p><p> </p><p>A list of the sites routinely used by the Armed Forces for training in urban environments is provided in the table below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>SITE</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Salisbury Plain Training Area</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Dartmoor Training Area</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Lulworth Range Complex</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Tregantle Training Area</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>East Kent Training Area</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Hythe Ranges</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Lydd Ranges</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Longmoor</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Bramley Training Area</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Pirbright Ranges</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Stanford Army Field Training Centre</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Fingerinhoe</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Sennybridge Training Area</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Swynnerton Training Area</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Caerwent Training Area</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Castlemartin Ranges</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Leek Training Area</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Nescliff Training Camp</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Magilligan Training Centre &amp; Ranges</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Ballykinler Tranining Centre &amp; Ranges</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Garelochhead Training Centre</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Catterick Training Area</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Warcop</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>British Army Training Unit Suffield – Canada</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>British Army Training Unit Kenya</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Sennylager Training Centre – Germany</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","6216","2019-10-31T14:59:44.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166635/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166635/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166635/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-10-28","Armed Forces: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether UK armed forces are undertaking urban training exercises in preparation for the UK leaving the EU without a deal.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","6215"
