"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166645","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-11-04","<p>The official statistics for judge sitting days (tables 5.1, 5.2 and 5.3 of the Civil Justice Statistics Quarterly, January to March 2019) were withdrawn on 5 September 2019, due to data discrepancies that were discovered after publication on 6 June 2019 and deemed potentially misleading to users. These discrepancies remain under investigation and, in line with the Code of Practice on Statistics, the Chief Statistician and Head of Profession decided to withdraw these tables until the investigations were complete as is normal practice. The revised figures will be published in due course, and will provide the total sitting days in Family, Civil and Crown courts.</p>","Croydon South","Chris Philp",,"2019-11-04T17:57:04.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166645/answer","Biography information for Chris Philp","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166645/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166645/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-10-28","Judiciary","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many days (a) recorders and (b) judges have sat in total in England in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","6329"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166646","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-11-05","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Dissolution.</p>","Tatton","Esther McVey",,"2019-11-05T16:12:57.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166646/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166646/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166646/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-10-28","Travellers: Caravan Sites","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what procedures should be followed by which bodies when non-Travellers live on Traveller sites.","false","Biography information for Andrew Selous","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","6288"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166647","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-11-04","<p>For many years leasehold developments have existed with peppercorn ground rents. In line with usual practice, the government’s intention would be to publish an impact assessment on zero ground rents for future leases, as part of taking primary legislation through Parliament.</p><p>In addition, Lord Best’s working group advising government on the regulation of property agents, which reported on 18 July, proposed that government consider extending regulation to freeholders. We are carefully considering all the recommendations in the report and will announce next steps in due course.</p>","Tatton","Esther McVey",,"2019-11-04T15:46:08.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166647/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166647/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166647/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-10-28","Leasehold","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on the viability of the leasehold sector of (a) regulating professional freeholders and (b) removing the financial value of ground rents; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jonathan Lord","Woking","Mr Jonathan Lord","6364"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166648","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-11-05","<p>The government has consistently made clear that building safety is the responsibility of the building owner. In line with usual practice, the government’s intention would be to publish an impact assessment on our leasehold reforms as part of taking primary legislation through Parliament.</p>","Tatton","Esther McVey",,"2019-11-05T14:17:07.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166648/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166648/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1166648/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-10-28","Ground Rent","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what assessment his Department has made of the potential effect of banning ground rents on the management of building (a) safety, (b) fire and (c) structural risk; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jonathan Lord","Woking","Mr Jonathan Lord","6365"
